          "value": "bleeding",
          "priority": 0
        }
      ],
      "description": "<p><strong>Max Ranks</strong>: 5</p><hr /><p>A Bleeding creature has suffered a minor abrasion to their flesh, causing slow blood loss if untreated.</p><ul><li><p>At the start of their turn, a bleeding creature takes 1d4 necrotic damage for each rank of Bleed they have.</p></li><li><p>A Bleeding creature cannot gain the benefits of a rest.</p></li><li><p>As an Action, a Bleeding creature may attempt to stop the bleeding by succeeding on a DC 15 Medicine check.</p></li><li><p>A creature who would gain a sixth (or more) ranks of the Bleeding condition immediately gains 5 ranks of the Lacerated condition, ending the Bleeding condition.</p><ul><li><p>The first time per rest a Bleeding creature would gain the Lacerated this way, they must succeed a DC 11 flat check, immediately taking the damage of their Lacerated ranks as they suffer a great wound.</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Outside of combat, every 10-minutes a creature suffers the effects of this condition as if a turn has passed in combat.</p></li></ul>",
